<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1397,2000]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,269,1398,1424]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">Male:</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[275,351,1397,1423]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1926,1951]" captionTargetBox="[171,1436,192,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lucihormetica yasuniana Vidlička, sp. n. Holotype—habitus, ♂. A, B—habitus, dorsal (A) and ventral (B) view (without the tip of abdomen); C—left hind wing. Photos A &amp; B taken by Roman Hergovits." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3367007/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
A–C, 7 A–G, 8 A–F. Head dark brown to black, with broad yellow spots over the antennal socket. Antennal sockets and proximal part of labrum yellow (
<figureCitation box="[771,867,1433,1460]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1926,1951]" captionTargetBox="[171,1436,192,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lucihormetica yasuniana Vidlička, sp. n. Holotype—habitus, ♂. A, B—habitus, dorsal (A) and ventral (B) view (without the tip of abdomen); C—left hind wing. Photos A &amp; B taken by Roman Hergovits." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3367007/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">Fig. 6 B</figureCitation>
). Compound eyes dark; intraocular distance large; ocelli not visible.Antennae short (but not preserved full length), reached at most half the body. Scapus, and meriston longer as wide, glossy; following 9–10 segments near square-shape, dark brown and glossy, nearly without setae; next 19–20 segments smaller, brown, dull, densely cover by small setae; following 5 segments small, yellow and at least 3 segments brown, dull.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1397,2000]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">
Pronotum wider than its length, brownish-yellow, bordered with elevated narrow black strip; elevated border of pronotal disc black, central part brownish-red with two bean-shaped spots (
<figureCitation box="[994,1090,1649,1676]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1926,1951]" captionTargetBox="[171,1436,192,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lucihormetica yasuniana Vidlička, sp. n. Holotype—habitus, ♂. A, B—habitus, dorsal (A) and ventral (B) view (without the tip of abdomen); C—left hind wing. Photos A &amp; B taken by Roman Hergovits." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3367007/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">Fig. 6 A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1397,2000]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">
Legs dark brown to black, glossy; trochanters and adjacent parts of coxae, and surrounding of genicular joints pale brown; tibiae short, armed with long and strong spines; arolia and pulvilli well-developed, yellow; claws simple and symmetrical. Anteroventral margin of front femur with a row of soft spines (only on distal half), and terminating in one larger spine (
<typeStatus box="[509,559,1794,1820]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">type</typeStatus>
C1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1397,2000]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">
Tegmina broad, coriaceous, brownish-yellow; left tegmen overlapped largely right one; venation very dens with number of cross-veins; along basal part of subcosta narrow black stripe, anal field separated by conspicuous claval furrow (
<figureCitation box="[242,337,1901,1928]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1926,1951]" captionTargetBox="[171,1436,192,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lucihormetica yasuniana Vidlička, sp. n. Holotype—habitus, ♂. A, B—habitus, dorsal (A) and ventral (B) view (without the tip of abdomen); C—left hind wing. Photos A &amp; B taken by Roman Hergovits." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3367007/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">Fig. 6 A</figureCitation>
). Membranous hind wings relatively short, greyish-brown, veins generally brown; venation plentiful with numerous cross-veins, mainly in remigium; remigium darker than anal field (
<figureCitation box="[1112,1207,1937,1964]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1926,1951]" captionTargetBox="[171,1436,192,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lucihormetica yasuniana Vidlička, sp. n. Holotype—habitus, ♂. A, B—habitus, dorsal (A) and ventral (B) view (without the tip of abdomen); C—left hind wing. Photos A &amp; B taken by Roman Hergovits." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3367007/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">Fig. 6 C</figureCitation>
); anal lobe folded at rest between CuP and 1A.
</paragraph>
