yasuniana
</emphasis>
Vidlička
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[667,726,1648,1672]" pageId="10" pageNumber="165" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Holotype—genitalia, ♂. A, B—ventral view, sheathed hook (A) and protruded hook (B); C, D—preputial spines, dorsal (C) and ventral (D) view, on D with part of L2d-sclerite [L2' on via]; Ehook R2 [L3']; F—cleft sclerite L1 [R3' and R4'].
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1790,2032]" pageId="10" pageNumber="165">
Abdomen dark brown to black, glossy; T2–T8 with yellowish band on lateral margins and pale band on distal margins; S3–S5 centrally with discreet yellowish spots (
<figureCitation box="[790,932,1826,1853]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1914,1939]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1893]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Lucihormetica yasuniana Vidlička, sp. n. Holotype—abdomen, ♂. A—dorsal view, B—ventral view; C—T8, T9 and supra-anal plate with cerci (dorsal view); D—subgenital plate (ventral view); E—right cercus (ventral view); F, G—left (F) and right (G) styli (ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3367009/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="165">Figs. 7 A, B</figureCitation>
). Supra-annal plate symmetrical, posteriorly with a superficial V-shaped incision in the middle; central part transversally with pale strip. Cerci ±10-segmented, segments on bases with narrow pale-brown line; ventral side very densely haired, dorsal side plain (
<figureCitation box="[1255,1424,1898,1925]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1914,1939]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1893]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Lucihormetica yasuniana Vidlička, sp. n. Holotype—abdomen, ♂. A—dorsal view, B—ventral view; C—T8, T9 and supra-anal plate with cerci (dorsal view); D—subgenital plate (ventral view); E—right cercus (ventral view); F, G—left (F) and right (G) styli (ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3367009/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="165">Figs. 7 C, D, E</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate slightly asymmetrical; distally widely rounded; styli small, dark; pale plate around right stylus (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1914,1939]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1893]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Lucihormetica yasuniana Vidlička, sp. n. Holotype—abdomen, ♂. A—dorsal view, B—ventral view; C—T8, T9 and supra-anal plate with cerci (dorsal view); D—subgenital plate (ventral view); E—right cercus (ventral view); F, G—left (F) and right (G) styli (ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3367009/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="165">Fig. 7 F</figureCitation>
) markedly bigger than left one (
<figureCitation box="[551,647,1970,1997]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1914,1939]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1893]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Lucihormetica yasuniana Vidlička, sp. n. Holotype—abdomen, ♂. A—dorsal view, B—ventral view; C—T8, T9 and supra-anal plate with cerci (dorsal view); D—subgenital plate (ventral view); E—right cercus (ventral view); F, G—left (F) and right (G) styli (ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3367009/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="165">Fig. 7 G</figureCitation>
), pale border extend from right to left stylus (
<figureCitation box="[1158,1255,1970,1997]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1914,1939]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1893]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Lucihormetica yasuniana Vidlička, sp. n. Holotype—abdomen, ♂. A—dorsal view, B—ventral view; C—T8, T9 and supra-anal plate with cerci (dorsal view); D—subgenital plate (ventral view); E—right cercus (ventral view); F, G—left (F) and right (G) styli (ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3367009/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="165">Fig. 7 D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1790,2032]" box="[199,466,2006,2032]" pageId="10" pageNumber="165">
Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[317,394,2006,2032]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1647,1672]" captionTargetBox="[166,1417,222,1586]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,211,1603]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lucihormetica yasuniana Vidlička, sp. n. Holotype—genitalia, ♂. A, B—ventral view, sheathed hook (A) and protruded hook (B); C, D—preputial spines, dorsal (C) and ventral (D) view, on D with part of L2d-sclerite [L2' on via]; Ehook R2 [L3']; F—cleft sclerite L1 [R3' and R4']." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3367011/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="165">Figs. 8</figureCitation>
A–F).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,152,755]" box="[199,1112,152,179]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Folds in the inner margin of membranous part of genital hook [L3’] inexpressive.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,152,755]" box="[199,532,189,215]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Preputial spines sparse, short.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,152,755]" box="[199,418,225,251]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,225,251]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,152,755]" box="[199,1240,261,288]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,261,287]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Etymology</emphasis>
. The new species is named according to the 
<typeStatus box="[829,877,261,287]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">type</typeStatus>
locality—NP Yasuni (
<collectingCountry box="[1128,1228,261,288]" name="Ecuador" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,152,755]" box="[199,717,296,324]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,296,323]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[359,452,297,323]" name="Ecuador" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[467,706,297,324]" country="Ecuador" name="Sucumbios" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Sucumbios Province</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,456,332,359]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
. The new species is closely related to 
<emphasis box="[904,1362,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Rocha e Silva" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[904,1061,334,359]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonica">L. amazonica</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Vidlička, 2019" authorityName="Vidlička" authorityYear="2019" box="[1074,1362,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yasuniana" status="sp. n.">Lucihormetica yasuniana</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1371,1437,333,359]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1371,1437,333,359]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Rocha e Silva" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[397,549,370,395]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonica">
<emphasis box="[397,549,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. amazonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by smaller body; tegmen markedly reaching over the body; dark coloration of tegmen is distinctly more simply; preputial spines on genitalia are more numerous and different arranged; the sclerotized part of genital hook is rectangular curved on inner side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,477,503]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Remarks</emphasis>
. From among thirteen members of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zompro &amp; Fritzsche" authorityYear="1999" box="[843,1006,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[843,1006,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">Lucihormetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the males of four species have very shortened tegmina (
<taxonomicName authority="(Walker, 1868)" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1868" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[373,660,513,540]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="interna">
<emphasis box="[373,483,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. interna</emphasis>
(Walker, 1868)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ramirez Perez, 1992)" authorityName="Ramirez Perez" authorityYear="1992" baseAuthorityName="Ramirez Perez" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[673,1035,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="osunai">
<emphasis box="[673,777,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. osunai</emphasis>
(Ramirez Pérez, 1992)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[1049,1185,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subcincta">
<emphasis box="[1049,1185,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. subcincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[1239,1380,514,539]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verrucosa">
<emphasis box="[1239,1380,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. verrucosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and three others (
<taxonomicName authority="(Ramirez Perez, 1992)" authorityName="Ramirez Perez" authorityYear="1992" baseAuthorityName="Ramirez Perez" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[303,672,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerdai">
<emphasis box="[303,406,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. cerdai</emphasis>
(Ramirez Pérez, 1992)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Zompro &amp; Fritzsche, 1999" authorityName="Zompro &amp; Fritzsche" authorityYear="1999" box="[688,1147,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fenestrata">
<emphasis box="[688,832,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. fenestrata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zompro, O. &amp; Fritzsche, I." box="[841,1147,549,575]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" pagination="211 - 219" refId="ref6749" refString="Zompro, O. &amp; Fritzsche, I. (1999) Lucihormetica fenestrata n. gen., n. sp., the first record of luminescence in an orthopteroid insect (Dictyoptera: Blaberidae: Blaberinae: Brachycolini). Amazoniana, 15 (3 / 4), 211 - 219." type="journal article" year="1999">Zompro &amp; Fritzsche, 1999</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fritzsche, 2003" authorityName="Fritzsche" authorityYear="2003" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grossei">
<emphasis box="[1206,1317,550,575]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. grossei</emphasis>
Fritzsche, 2003
</taxonomicName>
) have the tegmina that do not reach the end of abdomen. The tegmina of species 
<emphasis box="[1151,1311,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Rocha e Silva" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[1151,1307,586,611]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonica">L. amazonica</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Rocha e Silva, 1987)" authorityName="Rocha e Silva" authorityYear="1987" baseAuthorityName="Rocha e Silva" baseAuthorityYear="1987" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saebrai">
<emphasis box="[1320,1436,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. saebrai</emphasis>
(Rocha e Silva, 1987)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Rocha e Silva, 1979)" authorityName="Rocha e Silva" authorityYear="1979" baseAuthorityName="Rocha e Silva" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[453,878,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tapurucuara">
<emphasis box="[453,624,622,647]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. tapurucuara</emphasis>
(Rocha e Silva, 1979)
</taxonomicName>
are probably similar as in previous three species, but their pictures were probably made after amputation of abdomen because of preparation of genitalia. The descrip- tions of these three species do not mention the tegmina characteristics. In species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vrsansky, Fritzsche &amp; Chorvat" authorityYear="2012" box="[1049,1150,693,719]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luckae">
<emphasis box="[1049,1150,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. luckae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fritzsche, 2008" authorityName="Fritzsche" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zomproi">
<emphasis box="[1202,1321,694,719]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. zomproi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fritzsche, I." pageId="11" pageNumber="166" pagination="16 - 19" refId="ref5893" refString="Fritzsche, I. (2008) Two new species of cockroaches from Brazil and Venezuela. Arthropoda, 16 (3), 16 - 19." type="journal article" year="2008">Fritzsche, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
tegmen reach the end of abdomen. Only in case of 
<taxonomicName authority="Vidlička, 2019" authorityName="Vidlička" authorityYear="2019" box="[784,929,730,755]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Lucihormetica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yasuniana" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[784,929,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">L. yasuniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[936,999,729,755]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[936,999,729,755]" pageId="11" pageNumber="166" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
tegmen overreach the tip of abdomen.
</paragraph>
